System Shock 2;System Shock 2;System Shock 2;;videos\System Shock 2 (1999).mp4;OK;images\System Shock 2 (1999).webp;;Steam, Warez;Irrational Games, Looking Glass Studios;Electronic Arts, Nightdive Studios;11/08/1999;"System Shock 2 is a first-person shooter action role-playing survival horror video game for Microsoft Windows, Apple OS X and Linux. The title was designed by Ken Levine and co-developed by Irrational Games and Looking Glass Studios. Originally intended to be a standalone title, its story was changed during production into a sequel to the 1994 PC game System Shock; the alterations were made when Electronic Arts—who owned the System Shock franchise rights—signed on as publisher. System Shock 2 was released on August 11, 1999, in North America.";Role-playing (RPG), Shooter;https://video.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_trailers/238210/11489/5163a1ac1c44a160e91d8911fbd60c020d604ac0/1751246660/hls_264_master.m3u8?t=1447357878;steam_238210
